resources.string: The ODM version check has failed. This means your system is currently using a version of the proprietary binaries, which your Android is not build for. This will may work without further problems, but could also harm your device in the future.\n Please consider upgrading them as soon as possible. Commonly you could just update the oem partition(s) with the expected version - but for further reference please visit a guide for your specific device (you may press the help button below).
When you are the maintainer of this rom you should consider overriding the respective property to enforce the correct version or hide this warning.
Your system is running an unsupported version of the software binaries. Tap here to learn more!
